  <summary>12/11/1987--Introduced.
Authorizes the appointment of an Assistant Attorney General for State and Local Law Enforcement Matters. Sets forth the duties of the Assistant Attorney General, which include: (1) serving as an ombudsman for State and local law enforcement agencies with respect to matters involving the Department of Justice; and (2) providing staff support to coordinate the activities of the Bureau of Justice Assistance.</summary>
